      "creatureType": "Undead",
      "blurb": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p>Huge giants and other enormous creatures make powerful skeletons.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Made from bones held together by foul necromancy, skeletons are among the most common types of undead, found haunting old dungeons and forgotten cemeteries.</p><hr /><h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> the garrison that never went off duty — Kazavon's <strong>minotaur</strong> mercenaries (kept intruders out and his own troops <em>in</em>), slain by Mandraivus and risen as horned skeletal champions. Posted at B3 (2 per room), B17 (5), C1 (4), C13 (1), D2 (2 per turret), E3 (3, advanced); <strong>12 more</strong> walk patrol routes as wanderers. They raise alarms by dying.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
